Adelani Adepegba,Abuja The Interim Administrator of the Presidential Amnesty Programme, Col. Milland Dikio (retd.) on has met with some Niger Delta in Port Harcourt, the Rivers State capital. A statement on Tuesday by the Principal Information Officer, PAP, Lawson Alaenetonwa, said the Dikio was received by the General Coordinator of the Association of Niger Delta Monarchs of Nigeria, His Majesty, Okurakpo Odhe ll,  the Odio-Logbo Of Okugbe Isoko Kingdom, and his council on Monday at the association’s office in Port Harcourt. The statement said  Dikio disclosed that he wished to  draw from their wisdom as he embarked on the onerous task of repositioning the Presidential Amnesty Programme. The Interim Administrator further told the monarchs that his ultimate aim was for the programme to look at ways to cooperate with state governments, local governments and other agencies. This, he added, was to synergize and make the Niger Delta the safest place to live and do business in the country. Copyright PUNCH.
